\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5}{\ignorespaces The three questioning design patterns formalized in \textsc  {PrefQuest}. Each card shows the target abstraction level, an example question, a representative user response, and the structured state field updated by that pattern. AO targets individual object placements (A\textsuperscript  {+}); PE targets category-level organizing rules (P\textsuperscript  {+}); PI tests a system-inferred hypothesis and yields confirmed or rejected preferences (P\textsuperscript  {+}/P\textsuperscript  {$-$}).}}{12}{figure.caption.7}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:pattern-cards}{{5}{12}{The three questioning design patterns formalized in \textsc {PrefQuest}. Each card shows the target abstraction level, an example question, a representative user response, and the structured state field updated by that pattern. AO targets individual object placements (A\textsuperscript {+}); PE targets category-level organizing rules (P\textsuperscript {+}); PI tests a system-inferred hypothesis and yields confirmed or rejected preferences (P\textsuperscript {+}/P\textsuperscript {$-$})}{figure.caption.7}{}}
