\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {7}{\ignorespaces Overview of the \textsc  {PrefQuest} framework. At each dialogue turn, the Strategy Controller selects a questioning pattern (AO, PE, or PI) based on the current Structured Preference State. The corresponding Proposer generates a natural-language question; the Oracle (or real user) responds; the State Updater extracts structured evidence and updates $\mathcal  {A}^+$, $\mathcal  {P}^+$, $\mathcal  {A}^-$, $\mathcal  {P}^-$, and $\mathcal  {U}$. After the budget is exhausted, the Final Placement Planner uses the accumulated state to assign receptacles to all seen and unseen objects. The dashed gray path (Raw LLM) shows the baseline that bypasses the Structured Preference State and maps QA history directly to placements, degrading generalization on unseen objects.}}{17}{figure.caption.16}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:system-architecture}{{7}{17}{Overview of the \textsc {PrefQuest} framework. At each dialogue turn, the Strategy Controller selects a questioning pattern (AO, PE, or PI) based on the current Structured Preference State. The corresponding Proposer generates a natural-language question; the Oracle (or real user) responds; the State Updater extracts structured evidence and updates $\mathcal {A}^+$, $\mathcal {P}^+$, $\mathcal {A}^-$, $\mathcal {P}^-$, and $\mathcal {U}$. After the budget is exhausted, the Final Placement Planner uses the accumulated state to assign receptacles to all seen and unseen objects. The dashed gray path (Raw LLM) shows the baseline that bypasses the Structured Preference State and maps QA history directly to placements, degrading generalization on unseen objects}{figure.caption.16}{}}
